news.title: Panaji: Registered owners to get alert in case of bid to sell property
news.para: In the plan, Cabral said, owners would have to enlist their property and their contact details. If any person attempts to fraudulently sell the property, the owner, who may be anywhere in the world, will get an email informing him of the attempt.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to raze two more colonies
news.para: ​​As per notice put up by the estate office in the colony on Tuesday, the slum dwellers were given seven days’ time to vacate the government land. UT has declared all the structures on this government land as illegal.

news.title: Bombay HC quashes year-old FIR in Palghar against IndiaBulls Housing
news.para: A bench of justices PB Varale and SM Modak while pronouncing the order said the First Information Report (FIR) was an abuse of process of law. It allowed two quashing petitions -- one filed by a builder Atul Chordia and other by Indiabulls and others.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body constructing 24,192 Tidco housing units
news.para: APTIDCO chairman J Prasanna Kumar conducted a review meeting with the GVMC officials at the GVMC office on Tuesday.

news.title: RBI hikes interest rate by 40 bps to 4.40%
news.para: The Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) headed by RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das also raised the amount of deposits banks are required to maintain a cash reserve by 50 bps to 4.5 per cent to suck out Rs 87,000 crore of liquidity from the banking system.

news.title: Jaipur development body will seek list of colonies from MLAs for regularisation
news.para: A senior official said, “In a recent meeting, direction was given by the Jaipur Development Commissioner (JDC) to rope in public representatives as it will not only expedite the process, but help the JDA to achieve its target.”

news.title: Ludhiana: Residential areas fight for space amid big boom in commercial activities
news.para: ​A few residents had taken part in the meeting, demanding a concrete plan to decongest these areas. They said it is not possible to seal or demolish the structures, so creation of additional parking space is the best solution to the problem.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board earns Rs 120 crore from 177 units' sale in year
news.para: Officials have claimed it to be a record revenue for the CHB through auction in a single year. Yashpal Garg, chief executive officer (CEO), CHB, said he and senior officials personally visited the vacant units and analysed reasons for their unpopularity.

news.title: Muda pushes for vertical growth to counter land shortage in Mysuru
news.para: Mysuru being a heritage city with over 100 listed heritage sites, top officials are dilly-dallying the approval for the project, but Muda is hopeful of its ambitious project as the proposed location is beyond the core areas of zoning regulation.

news.title: Signature Global raises Rs 400 crore from HDFC Capital
news.para: The funding will be utilised for land acquisition and development of affordable housing projects in Haryana.

news.title: Tata Realty leases 1.56 lakh sq ft office space in Gurugram to Johnson Controls, PepsiCo
news.para: Tata Realty and Infrastructure Ltd, a 100 per cent subsidiary of Tata Sons Pvt Ltd, has leased over 1,56,000 square feet to Johnson Controls and PepsiCo.

news.title: Bengaluru: 40,000 apply for '1 lakh housing scheme'
news.para: The scheme envisages building 1 lakh houses in Bengaluru Urban district — in multiple locations spread across Anekal, KR Puram, Dasarahalli, Byatarayanapura, Mahadevapura, Yelahanka and Yeshwantpur — in phases.

news.title: Affordable housing finance companies' loan book to grow 17-20% in FY23: Study
news.para: As on December 31, 2021, the total loan book of AHFCs stood at Rs 66,221 crore and constituted about 6 per cent of the overall housing finance companies (HFCs) loan book.

news.title: Home First Finance reports 54% jump in profit to Rs 48 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income during January-March quarter of 2021-22 rose by 15 per cent to Rs 156 crore as against Rs 136 crore in the same period of 2020-21, Home First Finance said in a release.

news.title: SC ruling on retro effect of Benami Law keenly awaited
news.para: A plethora of transactions like cash transfers, property deals, and share issuances have come under the lens with the invocation of the Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Amendment Act, which came into effect from November 1, 2016 following the amendment of a 28-year-old ineffective law.
